cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.SOC, cs.DB, cs.HC 

The paper focuses on user modeling for point of interest recommendations in location-based social networks, which involves analyzing data and making recommendations based on user behavior. This falls under the categories of social networks (cs.SOC), information retrieval (cs.IR), and databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper discusses the structure and characteristics of LBSNs, which could fall under human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
